Hymettus
, s.d., Spruner, s.n. (as
E. sphaerocephalus
) (lecto-, G-BOIS [ G00765089 , digital photo!, Fig. 2 ];
isolecto-, G-BOIS[G00765089a, digital photo!, Fig. 3 ] ) .

Echinops albidus
was quoted for the Balkan Peninsula and for SE Italy according to Kožuharov (1976 , as
E. sphaerocephalus subsp. albidus
). In Italy , it is indicated as doubtful for Abruzzo and Campania though still recorded in Basilicata (
Conti et al. 2018
;
Bartolucci et al. 2018
). Thorough search did not reveal any records of the species from the reported localities in the Majella mountains ( Tammaro 1986 ). As these are the only findings published for Abruzzo , the species has been excluded from this region (
Conti et al. 2019
). Similarly the occurrence in Basilicata and Campania is not supported by any specimens in FI, APP and in HLUC herbaria, thus, at the given point, it is to be excluded from Italy at all.
